ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W1_CinemaSeatPlan

Class Name: CinemaSeatPlanner

Difficulty: Level 2 — Multi-Class Application

Estimated Time: 45–60 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 51 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Create a cinema seat reservation program using a two-dimensional array.
The program should create seat labels, process reservation requests,
update reserved seats, and print the final seating chart.

Requirements
- Use a two-dimensional String array to store seats.
- Use nested for loops to fill and print the seats.
- Use a SeatRequest object to store each reservation request.
- Validate row and column indexes before reserving a seat.
- Mark reserved seats as "XX".
- Count and print the number of available seats.

Learning Objective
Practice using multidimensional arrays with nested loops while organizing
reservation logic into multiple classes and methods.
